                <h1>Will Peel and Stick Wallpaper Damage Your Walls?</h1>
                <p>While peel and stick wallpaper offers a trendy, removable option for home decor, it can potentially damage walls upon removal. Improper application or prolonged adhesion can lead to paint peeling, drywall tears, or adhesive residue. To prevent damage, ensure surfaces are clean and smooth before installation and follow removal guidelines carefully.</p>
